{"build_type":"executable","description":"Batch package rename: reads {map, roots} from stdin, where map is an object {old_package_name: new_name, ...}. Applies every rename in one invocation (rename_one_package_by_name per entry, via rename_packages_from_map_loop). One call does the whole §10 mass rename, avoiding hundreds of separate tool runs. Caller must ensure the map is collision-free and no new name equals any not-yet-processed old name. Build artifacts' manifest target/entry are fixed separately afterward. Emits {status, count}. Reuses read_all_of_stdin, decode_entire_source_building_document, locate_named_member_inside_mapping, count_members_inside_container_value, rename_packages_from_map_loop, begin_empty_mapping_document_value, add_str_field, add_number_to_object, emit_result_object_onto_standard_output.","module_name":"perform-batch-package-rename-operations","package_name":"perform-batch-package-rename-operations","function_definitions":{"perform-batch-package-rename-operations":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"__argc","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"__argv","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_map","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"map"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_roots","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"roots"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_status","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"status"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"v_ok","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"ok"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_count","variable_type":"str","a